{
  "id": "the-cat-and-the-cock",
  "title": "The Cat and The Cock",
  "subtitle": "Aesop's Fables, Volume 05",
  "level": "A2-B1",
  "duration": 70.8,
  "audioFileName": "the-cat-and-the-cock.mp3",
  "sourceURL": "https://librivox.org/aesops-fables-volume-5-fables-101-125/",
  "textSourceURL": "https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/11339",
  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 16.48,
      "end": 20.6,
      "text": "The Cat and the Cock.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 21.54,
      "end": 27.12,
      "text": "A Cat pounced on a cock and cast about for some good excuse for making a meal of him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 27.12,
      "end": 32.56,
      "text": "For Cat's don't as a rule eat cocks, and she knew she ought not to.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 33.18,
      "end": 37.46,
      "text": "At last she said, you make a great nuisance of yourself at night by",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 37.46,
      "end": 41.78,
      "text": "crowing and keeping people awake, so I am going to make an end of you.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 42.34,
      "end": 46.8,
      "text": "But the Cock defended himself by saying that he crowed in order that men might",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 46.8,
      "end": 52.02,
      "text": "wake up and said about the day's work in good time, and that they really couldn't",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 52.02,
      "end": 53.46,
      "text": "very well do without him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 53.46,
      "end": 59.18,
      "text": "That may be, said the Cat, but whether they can or not, I'm not going without my dinner,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 59.92,
      "end": 61.78,
      "text": "and she killed and ate him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 62.7,
      "end": 66.6,
      "text": "The wand of a good excuse never kept a villain from crime.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 68.44,
      "end": 70.8,
      "text": "End of the Cat and the Cock.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
